desc:
Given an undirected graph with 40 nodes (0..39) and edges specified below. For each node, we also provide up to 2 neighbors with the largest degrees. Find a minimum vertex cover: a smallest set of vertices such that every edge has at least one endpoint in this set.

The input includes the edges of the graph and the top-2 neighbors for each node in format N[a,b,#c,#d], where a and b are the top-2 neighbors, #c is degree of a, and #d is degree of b. Format:
1. Set: The list of vertices in the minimum vertex cover.
2. Objective: The size of that set.
